The paper deals with the problem of optimal primary user emulation (PUE) attacks in cognitive radio networks, which involves spectrum sensing and dynamic channel access. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Information Theory (cs.IT), Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI), or Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. The paper also proposes online learning-based attacking strategies, which could fall under the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Finally, the paper specifically focuses on the security aspect of cognitive radio networks, which could indicate that it belongs to the Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-category.
